-- HP, Foxconn, Quanta, Inventec Choose Chongqing for Base, Taiwan's Bo Says
-- Chinmei Sung
-- 2010-06-30T04:02:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/hp-foxconn-quanta-inventec-choose-chongqing-for-base-taiwan-s-bo-says.html

          
          
             Hewlett-Packard Co., Foxconn
Technology Group, Quanta Computer Inc., and Inventec Co. will
build the world’s largest laptop production center in Chongqing,
the city’s Communist Party chief Bo Xilai said today.  
 The production base will have an annual production capacity
of 80 million laptops worth 500 billion yuan, Bo said.  
